work.work-title: Who puts his trust in God most just

credit.credit-words: Though fiercest foes my course oppose, A dauntless front I'll show them: My champion Thou, Lord Christ, art now, Who soon shalt overthrow them! And if but Thee I have in me With Thy good gifts and Spirit, Nor death nor hell, I know full well, Shall hurt me, through Thy merit.
Who puts his trust in God most just

direction-type.words: Who puts his trust in God
I rest me here without a fear;
By Thee shall all be given
That I can need, O Friend indeed,
For this life or for heaven.
O make me true, my heart
Keep me in peace for ever.
